      "writtenOn": "2026-03-06T15:06:48Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Do we also want to allow variants that do not return an error? That doubles the number of functions but may be quite convenient. As a compromise, we can only provide through PureFunc5 or so.\n\nAfter all, these functions are meant to make it convenient, as opposed to having the more indirect CallContext approach.\n\nE.g. PureFunc1e, vs PureFunc1\n\nI think NewPureFunc would be more idiomatic (see NewList, for instance). But also see naming comment below.",
      "revId": "065668779bc865ca3775c5b2702e4b079a79cf10",
      "serverId": "d5d70762-12d0-45a1-890d-524b12d3f735"
    },
    {
      "unresolved": false,
